#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Patch Java classes at build time with Quarkus Shim"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: synopsis
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Quarkus Shim lets you change the behavior of Java classes during the Quarkus build, with support for JVM mode, dev mode, and native executables."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"Applications often rely on Java classes from libraries that cannot be changed directly.\n"
"You may need to fix a small issue, add some logging, or adjust a return value while you wait for a change in the original library."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"https://github.com/quarkiverse/quarkus-shim[Quarkus Shim] is a Quarkus extension for these cases.\n"
"It lets you add, wrap, or replace behavior in a Java class during the Quarkus build."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"The change happens during augmentation.\n"
"There is no Java agent and no runtime instrumentation.\n"
"The transformed class works in JVM mode, dev mode, and native executables."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Add the extension"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Add Quarkus Shim to your application:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "You can find the latest version on https://central.sonatype.com/artifact/io.quarkiverse.shim/quarkus-shim[Maven Central]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Replace a method"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Imagine that a library contains this class:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"You want a different greeting, but the class belongs to a dependency.\n"
"Create a shim class and point it at `Greeter`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"`@Shim` selects the class to change.\n"
"`@ShimReplace` replaces the body of the selected method.\n"
"For an instance method, the first parameter receives the current object.\n"
"The other parameters and the return type match the original method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"Quarkus validates the shim during the build.\n"
"If the method does not exist or the signature is wrong, the build fails with an explanation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Wrap existing behavior"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"Sometimes you want to keep the original method and only adjust its result.\n"
"Use `@ShimAround` and call the original method through `ShimCall`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"This hook runs in place of the target method.\n"
"It can call the original behavior, transform the result, or return early."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Run code before and after a method"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"Use `@ShimBefore` when code should run at method entry.\n"
"Use `@ShimAfter` when code should run before a normal return:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"Both hooks must be static and return `void`.\n"
"The before hook can receive the target object and method arguments.\n"
"The after hook can receive the target object and returned value.\n"
"It only runs when the target method returns normally."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Access private members"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"A shim can use `ShimFields` and `ShimMethods` to reach private members.\n"
"For example, this alternative replacement updates a private counter and calls a private helper:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"The helpers cache their reflection work.\n"
"Quarkus Shim also registers target classes for reflection, so this approach works in native executables."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "Select one overloaded method"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "If a class has several methods with the same name, use `paramTypes` to select one of them:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "This shim changes `format(int)` and leaves other `format` methods unchanged."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "When is this useful"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"Quarkus Shim can help when you need a focused change in code that you do not own.\n"
"For example, you can use it for a temporary library fix, extra diagnostics, or a small compatibility adjustment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"It is best to keep each shim small and well tested.\n"
"A shim changes bytecode, so readers of the original class cannot see the new behavior there.\n"
"The shim should explain why the change exists and when it can be removed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"There are also limits.\n"
"Quarkus Shim can change application classes and indexed dependency classes loaded by Quarkus.\n"
"It cannot change JDK classes.\n"
"Abstract and native methods cannot be changed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid "What happens during the build"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"Quarkus Shim discovers shim classes and validates their hooks during augmentation.\n"
"It then uses the Quarkus bytecode transformation support and ASM to update the target classes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"This build time approach is the main reason the same shim can work across the usual Quarkus execution modes.\n"
"It also means mistakes are reported early, before the application starts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-07-17-quarkus-shim.adoc
msgid ""
"https://github.com/quarkiverse/quarkus-shim[Quarkus Shim] gives you a focused way to adapt code you do not own while keeping the change inside your Quarkus build.\n"
"Explore the project, try it in your application, and share your experience with us."
msgstr ""
